An agreement was reached between the MEC of Transport Willies Mchunu and taxi executives today at Dube Church, bringing the 4 day taxi strike to an end.As part of the agreement, Metro Police will not impound any taxis until Metro has assisted with the issuing of permits. It was also agreed that a special court will sit tomorrow where all taxi owners will pay a flat rate of R1500 for the release of the impounded taxis.The MEC of Transport has committed to assisting the taxis with the problems they are encountering in securing permits for their routes, and will personally be involved in the process of educating taxi associations on how they can secure permits.